The paper deals with constructing conditional probabilities from interval-valued probability assessments, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of linear systems also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the concept of coherence in probability theory is related to decision making and game theory, which fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
